+# Bottle anomaly detection
+
+This solution uses PaDiM with ImageNet-pretrained Wide ResNet-50-2 features.
+It fits a regularized Gaussian distribution at each feature-map location using
+only the normal images in `data/train`. Mahalanobis distance gives the anomaly
+map, and the image score is the mean of the highest-scoring 1% of pixels.
+
+Run from the task root:
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -r outputs/requirements.txt
+python outputs/train.py
+python outputs/infer.py
+```
+
+The first run may download the torchvision ImageNet weights if they are not
+already cached. Training writes `outputs/model.pt`. Inference writes
+`outputs/image_scores.json` and one 256x256 grayscale PNG per test image under
+`outputs/pixel_scores/`.
+
+Optional paths and runtime settings:
+
+```bash
+python outputs/train.py --train-dir data/train --model-path outputs/model.pt
+python outputs/infer.py --test-dir data/test_images --output-dir outputs
+```
