+# Feature-based anomaly detection
+
+This solution uses ImageNet-pretrained Wide ResNet-50-2 features and a
+PaDiM-style spatial Gaussian model. Features from `layer1`, `layer2`, and
+`layer3` are resized to a shared 64x64 grid. A deterministic subset of 256
+channels is modeled at every grid position using the mean and diagonal
+variance of the normal training images. Pixel scores are Mahalanobis distances;
+the image score is the mean of the highest-scoring 1% of pixels.
+
+All input images are resized to 256x256. Pixel maps are saved as single-channel
+16-bit PNG files at 256x256.
+
+## Run
+
+From the task root:
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -r outputs/requirements.txt
+python outputs/train.py
+python outputs/infer.py
+```
+
+The default commands read only `data/train/` and `data/test_images/`.
+ImageNet weights are downloaded by torchvision if they are not already cached.
+
+Optional arguments:
+
+```bash
+python outputs/train.py --train-dir data/train --model-out outputs/model.pt
+python outputs/infer.py --test-dir data/test_images --model outputs/model.pt \
+  --output-dir outputs
+```
