+# Feature-Based Anomaly Detection
+
+This solution uses ImageNet-pretrained Wide ResNet-50-2 features from layers 1,
+2, and 3. A fixed subset of channels is modeled with an independent Gaussian
+at each spatial location using only normal training images. Inference uses the
+standardized feature distance as a 64x64 anomaly map, smooths and resizes it to
+256x256, and averages the top 1% of map values for the image-level score.
+
+Run from the task root:
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -r outputs/requirements.txt
+python outputs/train.py
+python outputs/infer.py
+```
+
+The first run may download torchvision's ImageNet weights. Training writes
+`outputs/model.pt`. Inference writes `outputs/image_scores.json` and one
+single-channel 256x256 PNG per test image under `outputs/pixel_scores/`.
