+# Feature-Based Anomaly Detection
+
+This pipeline uses frozen ImageNet-pretrained ResNet-18 features from `layer1`,
+`layer2`, and `layer3`. The features are channel-normalized, resized to a common
+64x64 grid, and concatenated. Training fits a diagonal Gaussian independently at
+each spatial location using only normal images. Inference computes standardized
+feature distance, Gaussian-smooths the anomaly map, and aggregates its highest
+1% of pixels into an image score. Robust statistics from the training set map
+image scores to `[0, 1]`.
+
+## Run
+
+From the repository root:
+
+```bash
+python -m pip install -r outputs/requirements.txt
+python outputs/train.py
+python outputs/infer.py
+```
+
+The first run may download the standard torchvision ImageNet ResNet-18 weights.
+Inference creates `outputs/image_scores.json` and one 256x256 grayscale PNG per
+test image under `outputs/pixel_scores/`.
